{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, taste marketing frequently centers on health and functional benefits, addressing consumers' physiological needs.",
    "Companies increasingly employ artificial intelligence to identify emerging health trends, such as the demand for low-sugar or plant-based options, which can guide targeted product innovation.",
    "Moreover, flavor development in gustation tends to be more straightforward due to the predictability of human taste preferences, contrasting with the more subjective and varied preferences observed in olfaction.",
    "These insights underscore the importance of understanding both sensory modalities in order to develop effective marketing strategies and respond to consumer demands.",
    "Olfaction and gustation share several critical challenges that must be addressed to fully exploit AI's potential in sensory research."
  ]
}